  "texts": [
    "Using a dual backbone ResNext-101 with deformable convolution, DOLNet [92] achieve remarkable results over seven different benchmarks.",
    "Differently, HiM [93] and VSR[27] are state-of-the-art methods for DocBank [45] and [49], respectively, and use a RPN in conjunction with textual embedding and a graph structure for final document objects refinements in a multi-modal fashion.",
    "Considering a specific object of the document page, the GTE framework [94], composed of a series of vision-based neural networks, uses two levels of depth at table and cell level to detect table boundaries and its structure.",
    "Other relevant methods in this category are DeepLabV3+ [95], TNCR [67], and FigureSeer [37] for Figure Extraction and analysis.",
    "• Since document layouts are, or either contain, highly structured items, several researchers focused their efforts on graph-based techniques to tackle several tasks."
  ],
